race.description: In Memory Of Yvonne Boyle Hcp (C1)
race.comment: WHIL TO WIN (4) went to the front in a change of tactics last start and was never in danger over 900m at Newcastle. Should utilise the good gate and roll forward again. Looks ready to take on these better rivals. THIRD BASE (3) is a lightly raced five-year-old hasn't put in a bad run in his brief career. Showed pace but was claimed late last time out over this course and distance. Drawn to advantage and with the senior rider back on he should be right in contention. FAKE (10) did some work early on and gave plenty under pressure but was eventually edged out of the placings in a tight go over 1000m at this track recently. Each-way chance. NEVERMISTA (6) has been beaten under a length in his two runs this prep, both over 1000m. Gets a soft run from the inside stall and will be hard to hold out when produced. ARCHAIC FORCE (5) is one to monitor in betting first-up from an eight-week let-up.
